    "lore": {
      "key": "Tbl_Unit_Desc_91",
      "english": "Former Taimanin. Formerly one of the elders who oversaw the Igawa clan, she is the maternal aunt of the leader of all Taimanins, Igawa Asagi. In the past, she schemed in the clan’s power struggle but was defeated, losing both her hands in the process. Now, she works as an agent for the Internal Bureau of Intelligence and Research, commonly known as “IBIR.” Known for her mastery of intrigue and manipulation, she is an exceedingly dangerous individual.\n\nOnce a handler of falcons, she now wears cybernetic steel prosthetic arms, having lost her hands in a past conflict. A master of the Ninja Arts, her skill in close-quarters combat is said to rival even Momochi Toyo, reputed to have the finest melee combat ability in the Igawa clan.",
      "japanese": "Former Taimanin. Formerly one of the elders who oversaw the Igawa clan, she is the maternal aunt of the leader of all Taimanins, Igawa Asagi. In the past, she schemed in the clan’s power struggle but was defeated, losing both her hands in the process. Now, she works as an agent for the Internal Bureau of Intelligence and Research, commonly known as “IBIR.” Known for her mastery of intrigue and manipulation, she is an exceedingly dangerous individual.\n\nOnce a handler of falcons, she now wears cybernetic steel prosthetic arms, having lost her hands in a past conflict. A master of the Ninja Arts, her skill in close-quarters combat is said to rival even Momochi Toyo, reputed to have the finest melee combat ability in the Igawa clan.",
      "korean": "Former Taimanin. Formerly one of the elders who oversaw the Igawa clan, she is the maternal aunt of the leader of all Taimanins, Igawa Asagi. In the past, she schemed in the clan’s power struggle but was defeated, losing both her hands in the process. Now, she works as an agent for the Internal Bureau of Intelligence and Research, commonly known as “IBIR.” Known for her mastery of intrigue and manipulation, she is an exceedingly dangerous individual.\n\nOnce a handler of falcons, she now wears cybernetic steel prosthetic arms, having lost her hands in a past conflict. A master of the Ninja Arts, her skill in close-quarters combat is said to rival even Momochi Toyo, reputed to have the finest melee combat ability in the Igawa clan.",
      "chinese_simplified": "Former Taimanin. Formerly one of the elders who oversaw the Igawa clan, she is the maternal aunt of the leader of all Taimanins, Igawa Asagi. In the past, she schemed in the clan’s power struggle but was defeated, losing both her hands in the process. Now, she works as an agent for the Internal Bureau of Intelligence and Research, commonly known as “IBIR.” Known for her mastery of intrigue and manipulation, she is an exceedingly dangerous individual.\n\nOnce a handler of falcons, she now wears cybernetic steel prosthetic arms, having lost her hands in a past conflict. A master of the Ninja Arts, her skill in close-quarters combat is said to rival even Momochi Toyo, reputed to have the finest melee combat ability in the Igawa clan.",
      "chinese_traditional": "Former Taimanin. Formerly one of the elders who oversaw the Igawa clan, she is the maternal aunt of the leader of all Taimanins, Igawa Asagi. In the past, she schemed in the clan’s power struggle but was defeated, losing both her hands in the process. Now, she works as an agent for the Internal Bureau of Intelligence and Research, commonly known as “IBIR.” Known for her mastery of intrigue and manipulation, she is an exceedingly dangerous individual.\n\nOnce a handler of falcons, she now wears cybernetic steel prosthetic arms, having lost her hands in a past conflict. A master of the Ninja Arts, her skill in close-quarters combat is said to rival even Momochi Toyo, reputed to have the finest melee combat ability in the Igawa clan.",
      "spanish": "Former Taimanin. Formerly one of the elders who oversaw the Igawa clan, she is the maternal aunt of the leader of all Taimanins, Igawa Asagi. In the past, she schemed in the clan’s power struggle but was defeated, losing both her hands in the process. Now, she works as an agent for the Internal Bureau of Intelligence and Research, commonly known as “IBIR.” Known for her mastery of intrigue and manipulation, she is an exceedingly dangerous individual.\n\nOnce a handler of falcons, she now wears cybernetic steel prosthetic arms, having lost her hands in a past conflict. A master of the Ninja Arts, her skill in close-quarters combat is said to rival even Momochi Toyo, reputed to have the finest melee combat ability in the Igawa clan."
    },
