      "english": "Taimanin. Due to a curse inflicted by a demon she once fought, which is slowly taking over her, she sometimes becomes violent like a werewolf and starts destroying everything in her path. Because of this, she uses a specially formulated sedative from Gosha to suppress those impulses while carrying out missions, all the while seeking a way to break the curse.\n\nThe only daughter of a priest family and raised as its heir, she is not cute, but speaks and acts with calmness and kindness. However, as a sheltered young lady, she is often naïve about the ways of the world, which leads her teammates to tease her frequently.\n\nA Wind Art user, she combines the physical prowess of a wolf with Wind Art to excel in high‑mobility combat, wielding both a short katana and a demon‑piercing bow to employ versatile tactics unconstrained by distance.",
      "japanese": "Taimanin. Due to a curse inflicted by a demon she once fought, which is slowly taking over her, she sometimes becomes violent like a werewolf and starts destroying everything in her path. Because of this, she uses a specially formulated sedative from Gosha to suppress those impulses while carrying out missions, all the while seeking a way to break the curse.\n\nThe only daughter of a priest family and raised as its heir, she is not cute, but speaks and acts with calmness and kindness. However, as a sheltered young lady, she is often naïve about the ways of the world, which leads her teammates to tease her frequently.\n\nA Wind Art user, she combines the physical prowess of a wolf with Wind Art to excel in high‑mobility combat, wielding both a short katana and a demon‑piercing bow to employ versatile tactics unconstrained by distance.",
      "korean": "Taimanin. Due to a curse inflicted by a demon she once fought, which is slowly taking over her, she sometimes becomes violent like a werewolf and starts destroying everything in her path. Because of this, she uses a specially formulated sedative from Gosha to suppress those impulses while carrying out missions, all the while seeking a way to break the curse.\n\nThe only daughter of a priest family and raised as its heir, she is not cute, but speaks and acts with calmness and kindness. However, as a sheltered young lady, she is often naïve about the ways of the world, which leads her teammates to tease her frequently.\n\nA Wind Art user, she combines the physical prowess of a wolf with Wind Art to excel in high‑mobility combat, wielding both a short katana and a demon‑piercing bow to employ versatile tactics unconstrained by distance.",
      "chinese_simplified": "Taimanin. Due to a curse inflicted by a demon she once fought, which is slowly taking over her, she sometimes becomes violent like a werewolf and starts destroying everything in her path. Because of this, she uses a specially formulated sedative from Gosha to suppress those impulses while carrying out missions, all the while seeking a way to break the curse.\n\nThe only daughter of a priest family and raised as its heir, she is not cute, but speaks and acts with calmness and kindness. However, as a sheltered young lady, she is often naïve about the ways of the world, which leads her teammates to tease her frequently.\n\nA Wind Art user, she combines the physical prowess of a wolf with Wind Art to excel in high‑mobility combat, wielding both a short katana and a demon‑piercing bow to employ versatile tactics unconstrained by distance.",
      "chinese_traditional": "Taimanin. Due to a curse inflicted by a demon she once fought, which is slowly taking over her, she sometimes becomes violent like a werewolf and starts destroying everything in her path. Because of this, she uses a specially formulated sedative from Gosha to suppress those impulses while carrying out missions, all the while seeking a way to break the curse.\n\nThe only daughter of a priest family and raised as its heir, she is not cute, but speaks and acts with calmness and kindness. However, as a sheltered young lady, she is often naïve about the ways of the world, which leads her teammates to tease her frequently.\n\nA Wind Art user, she combines the physical prowess of a wolf with Wind Art to excel in high‑mobility combat, wielding both a short katana and a demon‑piercing bow to employ versatile tactics unconstrained by distance.",
      "spanish": "Taimanin. Due to a curse inflicted by a demon she once fought, which is slowly taking over her, she sometimes becomes violent like a werewolf and starts destroying everything in her path. Because of this, she uses a specially formulated sedative from Gosha to suppress those impulses while carrying out missions, all the while seeking a way to break the curse.\n\nThe only daughter of a priest family and raised as its heir, she is not cute, but speaks and acts with calmness and kindness. However, as a sheltered young lady, she is often naïve about the ways of the world, which leads her teammates to tease her frequently.\n\nA Wind Art user, she combines the physical prowess of a wolf with Wind Art to excel in high‑mobility combat, wielding both a short katana and a demon‑piercing bow to employ versatile tactics unconstrained by distance."
