    "icon": "123_Kagero",
    "lore": {
      "key": "Tbl_Unit_Desc_123",
      "english": "Taimanin. She devotes herself wholeheartedly—both in body and spirit—to pursuing Murakumo Gennosuke, the Taimanin swordsman who was exiled from the school of Ittoryu. Harboring feelings for him, she follows him wherever he goes, no matter the destination.\n\nShe is a practitioner of the restorative ninja art known as \"Rejuvenation Art\". However, even with this technique, she could not heal Gennosuke’s already ruined body; at best, she could only suppress his symptoms. Though she has learned the teachings of Ittoryu directly from Gennosuke, her swordsmanship remains average for a Taimanin.",
      "japanese": "Taimanin. She devotes herself wholeheartedly—both in body and spirit—to pursuing Murakumo Gennosuke, the Taimanin swordsman who was exiled from the school of Ittoryu. Harboring feelings for him, she follows him wherever he goes, no matter the destination.\n\nShe is a practitioner of the restorative ninja art known as \"Rejuvenation Art\". However, even with this technique, she could not heal Gennosuke’s already ruined body; at best, she could only suppress his symptoms. Though she has learned the teachings of Ittoryu directly from Gennosuke, her swordsmanship remains average for a Taimanin.",
      "korean": "Taimanin. She devotes herself wholeheartedly—both in body and spirit—to pursuing Murakumo Gennosuke, the Taimanin swordsman who was exiled from the school of Ittoryu. Harboring feelings for him, she follows him wherever he goes, no matter the destination.\n\nShe is a practitioner of the restorative ninja art known as \"Rejuvenation Art\". However, even with this technique, she could not heal Gennosuke’s already ruined body; at best, she could only suppress his symptoms. Though she has learned the teachings of Ittoryu directly from Gennosuke, her swordsmanship remains average for a Taimanin.",
      "chinese_simplified": "Taimanin. She devotes herself wholeheartedly—both in body and spirit—to pursuing Murakumo Gennosuke, the Taimanin swordsman who was exiled from the school of Ittoryu. Harboring feelings for him, she follows him wherever he goes, no matter the destination.\n\nShe is a practitioner of the restorative ninja art known as \"Rejuvenation Art\". However, even with this technique, she could not heal Gennosuke’s already ruined body; at best, she could only suppress his symptoms. Though she has learned the teachings of Ittoryu directly from Gennosuke, her swordsmanship remains average for a Taimanin.",
      "chinese_traditional": "Taimanin. She devotes herself wholeheartedly—both in body and spirit—to pursuing Murakumo Gennosuke, the Taimanin swordsman who was exiled from the school of Ittoryu. Harboring feelings for him, she follows him wherever he goes, no matter the destination.\n\nShe is a practitioner of the restorative ninja art known as \"Rejuvenation Art\". However, even with this technique, she could not heal Gennosuke’s already ruined body; at best, she could only suppress his symptoms. Though she has learned the teachings of Ittoryu directly from Gennosuke, her swordsmanship remains average for a Taimanin.",
      "spanish": "Taimanin. She devotes herself wholeheartedly—both in body and spirit—to pursuing Murakumo Gennosuke, the Taimanin swordsman who was exiled from the school of Ittoryu. Harboring feelings for him, she follows him wherever he goes, no matter the destination.\n\nShe is a practitioner of the restorative ninja art known as \"Rejuvenation Art\". However, even with this technique, she could not heal Gennosuke’s already ruined body; at best, she could only suppress his symptoms. Though she has learned the teachings of Ittoryu directly from Gennosuke, her swordsmanship remains average for a Taimanin."
    },
